<title>FRANCE: TAT/Air Liberte cabin crew seek mediation.</title>
<headline>TAT/Air Liberte cabin crew seek mediation.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The SNPNC cabin crew union on strike at TAT and Air Liberte, French subsidiaries of British Airways Plc, said on Tuesday it has asked chairman Marc Rochet to accept a mediator to break a weeks-old labour dispute.</p>
<p>Flight attendants at the two airlines went on strike on April 9 in protest against a planned merger which they say will mean a deterioration in work conditions and pay.</p>
<p>TAT and Air Liberte cockpit crews recently returned to work after agreeing a compromise for time-off, after a prolonged stoppage.</p>
